author: archie
msg: Handle architectures where object alignment can be greater than word
alignment (e.g., for doubles and longs). For objects containing one
or more primitive fields with strict alignment requirements but an odd
number of reference fields, force allocation with a skip word to even
out the number of references and therefore align the object.
